WEBVTT

00:02.200 --> 00:04.900
It's exactly as i described to you.

00:05.200 --> 00:06.900
Gary doesn't lie.

00:09.400 --> 00:12.100
Intimate but not small...
check.

00:12.200 --> 00:14.400
Character... double check.

00:14.500 --> 00:17.000
You see? Gary doesn't lie.

00:19.600 --> 00:20.800
And the best part...

00:21.200 --> 00:24.100
I've been working the owner for months,
convincing her to sell.

00:24.200 --> 00:25.300
You're getting in first.

00:25.400 --> 00:27.200
It's not even on the market yet.

00:32.400 --> 00:35.400
So, you like?

00:35.500 --> 00:36.900
The house? Yes.

00:37.200 --> 00:39.400
Gary? Maybe not.

00:41.300 --> 00:42.900
Good morning, everyone.

00:43.000 --> 00:45.300
Hey. Hello, Doris.

00:45.400 --> 00:47.500
I want you to meet your first
potential buyers...

00:47.600 --> 00:49.400
Fritz and Brenda.

00:49.600 --> 00:51.400
Thank you for coming.

00:51.900 --> 00:55.100
Would anyone like
a freshly baked cookie?

00:58.900 --> 01:00.200
Thank you.

01:00.300 --> 01:01.700
You're welcome.

01:03.700 --> 01:06.800
It's so homey here.
I'm surprised you want to leave.

01:06.900 --> 01:08.500
Oh, i don't, really.

01:08.600 --> 01:10.800
No, i put it on the market
last summer,

01:10.900 --> 01:12.900
and then i changed my mind.

01:13.100 --> 01:15.800
But the house has gone up
in value so much

01:15.900 --> 01:18.800
that everybody thinks i should
take the money and run.

01:20.100 --> 01:20.900
More coffee?

01:21.000 --> 01:22.000
- No, i think that...
- yes, please.

01:22.100 --> 01:23.100
Okay.

01:23.900 --> 01:28.800
You know, we raised
three children in this house.

01:29.300 --> 01:33.600
My husband, Tom...
he put those cabinets in himself.

01:33.700 --> 01:34.800
Oh.

01:35.100 --> 01:37.400
- More coffee?
- Yes, thank you.

01:38.700 --> 01:39.400
Hey.

01:39.900 --> 01:42.000
We can rip those out...
no problem.

01:43.700 --> 01:45.200
Goodness!

01:45.500 --> 01:47.400
More company!

01:53.200 --> 01:54.200
Deputy Chief Johnson.

01:54.300 --> 01:55.700
I thought you said this place
wasn't listed yet.

01:55.800 --> 01:56.900
It's not supposed to be.

01:57.000 --> 01:58.300
Yes, Lieutenant, what is it?

01:58.400 --> 02:01.100
Someone at my office must have noticed
it was back on the market.

02:01.300 --> 02:02.500
Why? What happened?

02:03.700 --> 02:04.900
He's how old?

02:05.800 --> 02:08.000
Oh, for heaven's sake.

02:08.500 --> 02:10.199
No, no.
I'll be right there.

02:10.800 --> 02:11.800
Thank you.

02:12.900 --> 02:14.500
What if we wanted to make an offer?

02:15.100 --> 02:16.000
What?

02:21.100 --> 02:23.800
Ö½éïµä×ö

02:24.600 --> 02:26.300
hey, chief.
Fax for you.

02:26.500 --> 02:29.200
- "Rules of escrow"?
- Thank you!

02:32.800 --> 02:35.500
So, this guy was pushing around
some sick old man

02:35.600 --> 02:37.600
in a wheelchair
near Hollywood Boulevard.

02:37.700 --> 02:39.900
A tourist finally gave him
a cellphone to call 911,

02:40.000 --> 02:42.300
but by the time
the paramedics got there,

02:42.400 --> 02:43.500
the guy in the wheelchair was dead,

02:43.600 --> 02:44.900
which might have been
the end of it, but...

02:45.000 --> 02:48.900
except our elderly gentleman here
claimed he murdered the victim.

02:49.100 --> 02:51.400
10 to 1,
here's what happened.

02:51.500 --> 02:53.200
"My heart!"

02:53.700 --> 02:55.100
"Help!

02:55.200 --> 02:56.300
Help!"

02:56.400 --> 02:59.000
And then hollywood division
pushed him our way

02:59.100 --> 03:01.200
so that they could enjoy their sunday.

03:01.400 --> 03:02.600
They're just following the rules, chief.

03:02.700 --> 03:07.300
Thing is, our old guy claims to have killed
six other people the same way.

03:08.500 --> 03:09.600
And how did he do that?

03:09.700 --> 03:10.500
He won't say.

03:10.600 --> 03:12.100
He won't tell us his name, either.

03:12.200 --> 03:14.800
He didn't have any i.d. On him,
and neither did the dead guy.

03:14.900 --> 03:15.800
All right.

03:17.800 --> 03:18.500
Okay.

03:18.600 --> 03:21.200
If i can determine that
this man's delusional,

03:21.300 --> 03:23.400
that he belongs to
the mental evaluation unit,

03:23.500 --> 03:25.400
then we can all go home
and save on overtime.

03:25.500 --> 03:26.800
In the meantime...

03:29.500 --> 03:31.100
detectives daniels and sanchez,

03:31.200 --> 03:32.800
please take a peek at missing persons.

03:32.900 --> 03:35.500
See if anyone's looking for
two nameless old men.

03:35.600 --> 03:39.400
Lieutenant provenza, please make sure that
our victim is on a gurney at the morgue.

03:39.500 --> 03:41.100
And, lieutenant tao,

03:41.800 --> 03:45.900
if you wouldn't mind sending this fax

03:46.400 --> 03:48.700
to the number on the cover sheet...

03:48.800 --> 03:51.400
it's some, um,
thingy for my real-estate agent.

03:51.500 --> 03:53.500
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

04:00.600 --> 04:02.100
Good morning, sir.

04:02.500 --> 04:04.700
I'm deputy chief brenda leigh johnson.

04:05.600 --> 04:07.300
Could you please tell me your name?

04:08.900 --> 04:11.000
How about the name of the man
who died?

04:11.300 --> 04:12.600
I murdered him...

04:13.000 --> 04:15.400
and the others...
i killed them all.

04:15.800 --> 04:17.300
And how did you do that?

04:17.800 --> 04:19.100
Poison.

04:19.800 --> 04:22.600
You know that you poisoned
a total of seven people,

04:22.700 --> 04:24.400
but you don't know your name?

04:24.500 --> 04:27.000
Who says i don't know my name?

04:27.600 --> 04:31.400
A deputy chief, huh?
That's pretty impressive.

04:31.600 --> 04:34.600
There's... what? ...12 of you
in the whole department?

04:35.300 --> 04:38.200
Sir, there are several
inconsistencies to your story.

04:38.300 --> 04:42.900
I actually remember that
detective provenza guy who put me in here.

04:43.000 --> 04:46.800
He was a highly motivated
young man.

04:47.800 --> 04:49.300
Bet your sweet ass i was.

04:49.400 --> 04:50.900
Have you been arrested before?

04:51.100 --> 04:54.100
I spent some time here
when i was younger.

04:55.100 --> 04:58.800
What is it about my story
that's inconsistent?

04:59.300 --> 05:01.600
Well, you claim you tried
to poison someone,

05:01.700 --> 05:03.600
and yet, you called 911.

05:04.000 --> 05:06.000
If you were <i>really</i> trying
to murder someone,

05:06.100 --> 05:07.400
why call for help?

05:07.800 --> 05:11.700
Well, uh, i wanted to see
what it was like...

05:11.800 --> 05:13.400
dying, you know?

05:13.800 --> 05:16.800
I didn't watch the others,
but it went on too long,

05:16.900 --> 05:18.000
and i chickened out.

05:18.100 --> 05:19.200
All right, uh, sir,

05:19.300 --> 05:22.300
l-i'm afraid that you might not be competent
to speak on your own behalf...

05:22.400 --> 05:24.200
you're worried about my sanity, huh?

05:24.300 --> 05:26.500
I have a right to remain silent.

05:26.600 --> 05:28.800
Anything i say can and will
be used against me

05:28.900 --> 05:29.800
- in a court of law.
- Sir.

05:29.900 --> 05:31.200
I have a right to an attorney.

05:31.300 --> 05:32.500
If i cannot afford one,

05:32.600 --> 05:33.700
- et cetera, et cetera.
- Sir.

05:33.800 --> 05:35.300
Blah, blah, blah.

05:35.400 --> 05:38.200
Look, let me make something
completely clear...

05:38.300 --> 05:40.900
i do not want a lawyer.
Understood?

05:41.400 --> 05:43.800
And if you don't know
how to assemble your case,

05:43.900 --> 05:45.700
let me give you a little hint...

05:46.000 --> 05:47.900
bernard kaplan.

05:48.600 --> 05:49.700
Is that your name?

05:49.900 --> 05:53.200
No, it's the name
of your dead john doe.

05:53.800 --> 05:56.500
And i'll trade you the names
of the other six people i killed

05:56.600 --> 05:58.800
if you'll give me something to eat.

06:03.800 --> 06:05.700
Names, please.

06:10.800 --> 06:13.200
Lieutenant provenza,
i'm almost afraid to ask you this...

06:13.300 --> 06:15.700
do you remember anything
about this old man?

06:15.800 --> 06:18.000
Well, if you twisted my arm,
i'd say he looks familiar.

06:18.100 --> 06:19.300
That's about it.

06:21.800 --> 06:24.800
Chief, i ran, uh,

06:24.900 --> 06:28.700
"rumple's" prints through afis
along with bernard kaplan...

06:28.800 --> 06:30.300
no hits on either man.

06:34.400 --> 06:37.300
Tao, what's a rumplestiltskin?

06:38.000 --> 06:39.600
It's a fairy tale.

06:39.800 --> 06:41.600
There's this old dwarf
who won't tell the queen his name,

06:41.700 --> 06:44.300
- and she has to guess it in order to...
- uh-huh.

06:45.500 --> 06:48.600
Well, if rumplestiltskin
<i>has</i> wandered away from home,

06:48.700 --> 06:50.200
it's been less than 24 hours.

06:50.300 --> 06:52.900
Missing persons hasn't generated
a report yet.

06:53.300 --> 06:54.500
All right.
Sergeant gabriel,

06:54.600 --> 06:55.900
let's head over
to the coroner's office,

06:56.000 --> 06:58.300
see if we can get
some death certificates...

